Saturday's visit was to happen at his mother's home in Barree Township.

But once at the home, Mr Ayers got into a fight with his Michael's mother, Hollie Jo Ayers, and shot her in the legs and arm with a .40 caliber handgun.

He then intentionally shot his son, police said.

Mr Ayers placed the child's body in the back of his vehicle but the wounded woman retrieved the body before Ayers shot her again in the face, police said. He also fired at his mother but missed.

